  "response_text": "A Pine-Sol bottle stands upright on a light kitchen floor in front of warm wooden cabinets. The clear plastic bottle is filled with amber liquid and has a green label with large yellow “Pine-Sol” lettering. Around it, small animated green pine-tree shapes whirl and dart across the floor like scrubbers, leaving blurred green trails as they circle the bottle. Some pass close to the bottle’s base, while others sweep in from the sides and above, making the product appear surrounded by energetic cleaning power.\n\nThe scene shifts to a dark, studio-like background where a large Pine-Sol bottle stands at the far left, taller and more prominent than a row of smaller amber bottles beside it. The smaller bottles have white circular labels marked with a large red “2,” suggesting competing “number two” pine cleaners. A green streak, like the fast-moving pine-tree scrubbers, sweeps along the row from the right. As it passes, the line of “2” bottles appears to recede and diminish, leaving the Pine-Sol bottle dominant on the left.\n\nIn a kitchen, the view looks upward toward a white range hood against blue walls and wooden ceiling beams. A broad yellow-brown greasy stain spreads across the hood’s front surface. A small green pine-tree scrubber moves along the stained area, as if attacking the grime. Shelves with small kitchen items sit on the wall below.\n\nA bathroom floor appears from above, with white hexagonal tiles dotted by small black accents. A toilet is visible to the right and the edge of a bathtub to the left. Across the floor, the large word “STAPH” is written in mottled yellow-green letters, representing germs or contamination on the bathroom surface.\n\nThe product returns in a dramatic close-up. The Pine-Sol bottle fills the left side, its green label and bold yellow “Pine-Sol” name large and tilted. On the red band near the bottom of the label, the words “CLEANS,” “DISINFECTS,” and part of “DEODORIZES” are visible. To the right, thick green three-dimensional letters “VED” attach visually to the product name, forming the wordplay “Pine-Solved.”\n\nFinally, a pale floor is shown from above with a large tan, smeared patch of grime in the center. The animated green pine-tree scrubbers rush in from the edges and begin sweeping over the dirty patch. As they move, oversized yellow letters spelling “Pine-Sol” slide into view beneath or through the grime, and the stain fades away. More green letters appear at the right to complete “Pine-Solved.” By the end, the floor looks clean and bright, with the bold yellow “Pine-Sol” name and green “VED” lettering left clearly visible while the little pine scrubbers continue moving around it.",
